All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Command
Class stores values about state of an idea and can be interacted with by the UserStory class to fetch this data.
Command.CommandValue
Enum is used to keep track of possible states of a story because of a limited number of options
CommandTest
Tests command class
Project
Class stores many user stories in an ArrayList.
ProjectReader
Method handles input from project files and reads them into the program so the projects can be interacted with.
ProjectReaderTest
Tests capabilities to read projects in from a file
ProjectTest
Tests Project class.
ProjectWriter
Method handles writing projects to files.
ProjectWriterTest
Tests capabilities of program to write projects to a file for long term storage.
RequirementsManager
Method serves as the controller for the rest of the backend of this program, and is the only class that the GUI must interact with to control the program.
RequirementsManagerGUI
Container for the RequirementsManager that has the menu options for new project files, loading existing files, saving files and quitting.
RequirementsManagerTest
Tests RequirementsManager controller class
UserStory
Method stores all information related to a UserStory and its state.
UserStoryTest
Tests UserStory object.
